---
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>CNN Detection - Xi Lin</title>
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16 sm:px-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">Back to home</a>
      <p class="mt-6 text-sm font-mono text-blue-600">IEEE IPIC 2023 | First Author</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Research on Object Detection of Robotic Based on Convolutional Neural Network</h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-4xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        This was an earlier undergraduate competition project built around a SLAM-oriented UAV pipeline. The practical goal was to combine YOLOv5 perception with VINS-Fusion so that object detection and visual navigation could run in one system for target-aware flight and tracking experiments.
      </p>

      <section class="mt-10 rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-gray-50 p-6 sm:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Project Framing</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
          The contribution here was less about a polished paper and more about making the pipeline work end to end for a competition setting: reproducing VINS-Fusion, integrating YOLOv5 into the perception stack, and validating that the UAV platform could use the resulting detections for downstream navigation-related behavior.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <img src="/assets/projects/cnn-accuracy-plot.png" alt="Detection accuracy comparison" class="w-full object-contain" />
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[28px] border border-gray-200 bg-white p-4">
          <img src="/assets/projects/undergrad-trajectory.png" alt="VINS-Fusion real trajectory" class="w-full object-contain" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
